title: Sales Representatives of Services, Except Advertising, Insurance, Financial Services, and Travel
descr: Sell services to individuals or businesses. May describe options or resolve client problems.
alt_titles: Sales Consultant, Sales Development Representative, Accounts Manager, Accounts Representative, Technical Sales Representative, Automobile Club Membership Sales Agent, Automotive Sales Consultant (Auto Sales Consultant), Business Services Sales Representative, Business-to-Business Sales Representative, Client Relationship Consultant, Salesman, Customer Service Representative (Customer Service Rep), Customer Service Sales Representative (Customer Service Sales Rep), Field Sales Consultant, Field Sales Representative, Sales Representative (Sales Rep), Independent Sales Representative, Inside Sales and Customer Service Representative (Inside Sales and Customer Service Rep), Inside Sales Representative, Marketing Representative, Member Services Representative (Member Services Rep), Membership Representative (Membership Rep), Membership Solicitor, Outside Sales Representative, Pest Control Service Sales Agent, Product Specialist, Route Sales Representative (Route Sales Rep), Sales Agent
experience: Some previous work-related skill, knowledge, or experience is usually needed. For example, a teller would benefit from experience working directly with the public.
education: These occupations usually require a high school diploma.
job_training: Employees in these occupations need anywhere from a few months to one year of working with experienced employees. A recognized apprenticeship program may be associated with these occupations.
example: These occupations often involve using your knowledge and skills to help others. Examples include orderlies, counter and rental clerks, customer service representatives, security guards, upholsterers, tellers, and dental laboratory technicians.
svp_desc: Individuals workers typically need anywhere from minimum of 3 and 6 months- up to 2 years- to learn the techniques, acquire the information, and develop the facility needed for average performance in specific situations.
